title: Grateful Dead Live at Ventura County Fairgrounds on 1983-07-30
description:
Set 1

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, It's All Over Now, Brown Eyed Women, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues, Cassidy, Loser, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Sugaree, Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Child of Boundless Seas First set is a 3.5. The performance is lackluster and the soundboard has issues supporting Jerry. He’ll be soloing out front and then he fades to the back in sound level. 

Second set is a solid 5. Sound quality is consistently good, playing inspired and an unusual pre drums set list. China Doll has an ugly vocal moment, but overall quite nice. The gem of the show is Black Peter. Played with deep emotion and howling feedback in the break! 🥳
